    "For convergent and discriminant validity, AVE (Average Variance Extracted), MSV (Maximum Shared Variance), and ASV (Average Shared Variance) values were calculated.",
    "Convergent validity suggests AVE > 0.5, CR > 0.7, and CR > AVE, while discriminant validity requires MSV < AVE, ASV < AVE, and √AVE > inter-factor correlations (Gürbüz, 2019).",
    "Table 6 presents the CR, AVE, MSV, and ASV values and correlation coefficients for the factors in the ChatGPT Usage Scale for foreign language learners.",
    "According to the results in Table 6, all factors exhibit high reliability, with CR values exceeding 0.70.",
    "The AVE values for the factors are lower than the CR values, above 0.5, indicating convergent validity."
